{"cursor":"19881","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"{{Infobox Non-profit\n| Non-profit_name = Conservation International Non-profit_logo = Non-profit_type\n| = founded_date = 1987 founder = Spencer Beebe and Peter Seligmann location =\n| Arlington, Virginia origins = key_people = Peter A. Seligmann (Chairman &\n| CEO) Rob Walton (Executive Committee Chairman) Russell A. Mittermeier\n| (President) Niels Crone (COO) Harrison Ford (Vice-chair) area_served =\n| product = Global Conservation Fund focus = Climate change, freshwater\n| security, health, food security, biodiversity, cultural services method =\n| revenue = FY 2010: US $77.8 million; FY 2009: $ 116.1 million endowment = num_volunteers = num_employees = 900\n| num_members = subsib = owner = Non-profit_slogan = homepage =\n| http://www.conservation.org dissolved = footnotes =\n}}\n\n'Conservation International' ('CI') is a nonprofit environmental organization\nheadquartered in Arlington, Virginia. The organization's mission is to protect\nnature, and its biodiversity, for the benefit of humanity.\n\nCI is one of the largest conservation organizations headquartered in the United\nStates, though its field work is done in other countries. It has 900+\nemployees, more than 30 global offices, and more than 1,000 partners around the\nworld. Since its inception in 1987, CI has contributed to\nthe protection of more than 260 million acres of land and sea â including places such as the Phoenix Islands Protected\nArea, the largest UNESCO World Heritage Site in the world.\n\nFrom its origins as an NGO dedicated to protecting tropical biodiversity, CI has\nevolved into an international organization with influence among governments,\nscientists, charitable foundations, and business.\n\nCI has been criticised for links to companies with a poor environmental record\nsuch as BP, Cargill, Chevron, Monsanto and Shell and for allegedly offering\ngreenwashing services. http://www.theecologist.org/News/news_analysis/87724-\n1/conservation_international_agreed_to_greenwash_arms_company.html ht-\ntp://www.thenation.com/article/wrong-kind-green CI has also been chastised\nfor poor judgment in its expenditure of donors' money.\n","linknr":328,"url":"Conservation_International","recorded":1376416733,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Conservation_International&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Conservation_International&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Conservation_International","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.visualEditor.viewPageTarget.noscript&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","#mw-navigation","#p-search","/wiki/File:CIlogo.svg","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/6e/CIlogo.svg/200px-CIlogo.svg.png","/w/index.php?title=Spencer_Beebe&action=edit&redlink=1","/w/index.php?title=Peter_Seligmann&action=edit&redlink=1","/wiki/Headquarters","/wiki/Arlington_County,_Virginia","/wiki/S._Robson_Walton","/wiki/Harrison_Ford","/wiki/Product_(business)","/wiki/Attention","/wiki/Climate_change","/wiki/Water_security","/wiki/Health","/wiki/Food_security","/wiki/Biodiversity","/wiki/Revenue","#cite_note-2010report-1","/wiki/Employees","/wiki/Website","http://www.conservat